## Evidence policy

- Treat Hermes Kanban as the worker coordination source of truth.
- Cite board/task IDs and relevant branch/PR/test/verdict evidence for work claims.
- Do not claim another profile completed work unless durable evidence exists.

## Communication policy

- Discord is the user surface through Atlas in v1.
- Worker profiles communicate through Kanban comments, task state, and dependencies.
- Do not use Discord as a worker-to-worker bus.

## Knowledge policy

- Kanban is mission evidence, not long-term knowledge.
- Durable Team Nexus conventions belong in docs, profile specs, AGENTS.md, or repo-visible skills.
- Do not store task progress as long-term memory.
